pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=325.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Mace of the Explorer</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Wamba, did you ever get this mace-from-hell? If not, we have to get this thing! I found this great detailed walkthrough on the CoD boards, and I'm always up for killing a few mosswarts (they annoy me almost as much as mites).<br>
<br>
<br>
1) Visit Olivier Rognath (NPC), in the center of Eastham. Talk to him for the initial hint about this quest.<br>
<br>
2) The no-drop no-give Banderling Mace Shaft (500 BU, 10p) comes from the Banderling Conquest Dungeon(BCD) west of Sawato (29.0s 50.4e, no<br>
level restriction). The description says &quot;Combine with Mace head to make a ceremonial weapon&quot;.<br>
<br>
To reach Mace Shaft<br>
----------------------------------------<br>
* Shortly after entering, there is a room with left and right paths.<br>
* Take right-hand path<br>
* Follow downward quite a ways.<br>
* Eventually, reach a doorway where cave walls convert to brick-wall large room.<br>
* There is a Banderling Chief, a few Guards, and a few other Banderlings inside.<br>
* Mace Shaft will be on the floor in the large room(about a 3-minute respawn).<br>
* There is a doorway nearby leading to a surface portal.<br>
<br>
To reach &quot;A Battered Leather Journal&quot;<br>
----------------------------------------<br>
* Shortly after entering, there is a room with left and right paths.<br>
* Take left-hand path<br>
* Follow downward quite a ways.<br>
* Eventually, reach a wooden door.<br>
* Open door, enter the room. Journal is on the floor.<br>
* If you reach the room with the Desk and Banderling Captain, you have gone too far.<br>
<br>
<br>
3) The no-drop no-give Mace Head comes from the Mosswart Mayhem Maze between Uziz and Al-Arqas (25.3S, 19.4E, no level restriction).<br>
<br>
To reach the Mace Head<br>
----------------------------------------<br>
* As you enter, there is a trifurcation. <br>
* Take the right-hand path. <br>
* Take the fourth branch on the right.<br>
* Bear left at first fork.<br>
* Bear right at immediate next fork.<br>
* Proceed down hall (it should have a 'misty haze' in the air).<br>
* Pass by a left branch - do not take it.<br>
* Go down ramp.<br>
* There will be two Goldenback Tuskers there on a short respawn.<br>
* Mace Head is laying on the floor (about a 3 minute respawn).<br>
* Proceed back up ramp.<br>
* Take first right-hand branch to reach a surface portal.<br>
<br>
To reach &quot;A Dry Withered Leather Bound Journal&quot;<br>
------------------------------------------------<br>
* As you enter, there is a trifurcation. <br>
* Take the right-hand path. <br>
* Take the first branch on the right.<br>
* Bear left at rounded fork.<br>
* Take first left.<br>
* At end of hallway is a room with two Barker Mosswarts.<br>
* The Journal will be laying on the floor.<br>
* It is no-give, but it is droppable. (only 10 BU).<br>
<br>
4) Combine the Mace Shaft with the Head to form the Ceremonial Banderling Weapon. (1500 BU, no-drop no-give).<br>
<br>
5) Give the Ceremonial Weapon to Olivier Rognath and he will return to you the Mace of the Explorer.<br>
<br>
6) Optionally, give Olivier the texts, and he will speak some clues.<br>
<br>
<br>
Mace of the Explorer stats are:<br>
-----------------------------------<br>
9-14, Bludgeon<br>
Speed 40<br>
Casts BD III &amp; HS III<br>
Diff 15, Mace &gt; 129<br>
750 BU<br>
700p <br>
No-drop<br>
No-give<br>
No-drop-on-death??<br>
